This paper is likely to belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category as it deals with genetic algorithms, which are a type of evolutionary algorithm. It may also belong to the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category as it presents a Markov Chain framework for analyzing the performance of genetic algorithms. Additionally, it could be classified under Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) as genetic algorithms are a popular optimization technique in AI. The paper also involves mathematical analysis and optimization, which could place it in the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Finally, the paper's focus on analyzing the performance of different algorithms could make it relevant to the Game Theory (cs.GT) sub-category.
